  "icon_variant": "filled",
  "workflow_system": "nf-core",
  "notes_content": "<h2>Alpha Diversity</h2><p>Three QIIME2 alpha-diversity metrics compute within-sample structure: <b>Shannon entropy</b> combines richness and evenness; <b>Observed features</b> counts unique ASVs (pure richness); <b>Faith's PD</b> sums branch lengths across the ASVs in a sample (phylogenetic spread). A fourth metric \u2014 <b>Pielou's evenness</b> \u2014 appears in the per-sample table and habitat-faceted boxplot.</p><p>The rarefaction tab strip lets you switch between the three depth-dependent metrics. If a curve hasn't asymptoted at the maximum sequencing depth, the sample is under-sequenced for that metric and downstream comparisons should be treated cautiously.</p>",
